dataIdInfo.idAbs:
Slums of Dhaka 2010

Polygons representing the delineations of slums larger than 1 acre in the Dhaka Metropolitan Area as seen in 2010 Quickbird images. Associated data table contains 92 entries according to the number of wards or unions in which they were found. Specifically, ‘FID’ is an index for the shapefile, while ‘Shape’ gives information about the feature type, which in our case in a polygon.Furthermore,it contains the column ‘ward_union’ that gives the number or name, in which ward or union they were found, respectively. Furthermore, the column ‘SUM_area_a’ gives the total slum area by ward/union in acre, while the column ‘SUM_area_s’ gives the total slum area by ward/union in m2.
